<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="129" pageId="1" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[113,1089,1406,1589]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,449,1406,1429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
Description of male 
<typeStatus box="[344,444,1406,1429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Colouration: Head capsule, mouthparts, antennae, pro- and mesothorax, legs, sides and apices of elytra, sternum VIII and pygidium yellow to orange; eyes, metathorax, scutellum and elytra (except sides, apices and suture) black; elytral suture and remaining abdomen lightened to brownish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[113,1089,1406,1589]" lastBlockId="3.[113,1089,220,595]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="128" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
Head capsule broader than long, with coriaceous microsculpture and fine whitish setae diverging towards compound eyes. Apical maxillary palpomere polygonal in outline (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1075,1566,1589]" captionStart="Figs 5–8" captionStartId="3.[113,150,1516,1535]" captionTargetBox="[188,1001,650,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[184,1019,624,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–8. Details of holotype of Colotrema socotrana sp. nov.5 – left maxillary palpus, ventral; 6 – pygidium, ventral view; 7 – sternite VIII, dorsal view; 8 – median lobe, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325783/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Scapus elongate, clavate, as long as pedicel and antennomere I together; adjoining antennomeres longer than broad.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325779" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5325779" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325779/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" startId="2.[151,188,1541,1560]" targetBox="[196,1075,222,1482]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1129,1541,1587]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
Figs 1–4. Habitus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1979" box="[327,417,1541,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[327,417,1541,1560]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Colotrema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 1–2 
<taxonomicName authority="Plonski, 2017" authorityName="Plonski" authorityYear="2017" box="[463,643,1541,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socotrana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[463,643,1541,1560]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Colotrema socotrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[647,716,1541,1560]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 1 – female allotype; 2 – male paratype #1; 3 – 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1979" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assirensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">C. assirensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="WITTMER W." box="[240,365,1568,1587]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" pagination="186 - 192" refId="ref2866" refString="WITTMER W. 1979: Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Malachiidae, Dasytidae, Karumiidae. Fauna of Saudi Arabia 1: 186 - 192." type="journal article" year="1979">Wittmer, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 4 – 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1980" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1980" box="[406,715,1568,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="testacea" subSpecies="wajjensis">
<emphasis box="[406,585,1568,1587]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">C. testacea wajjensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="WITTMER W." box="[590,715,1568,1587]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" pagination="114 - 118" refId="ref2896" refString="WITTMER W. 1980: Fauna of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Drilidae, Malachiidae, Prionoceridae (2. Beitrag). Fauna of Saudi Arabia 2: 114 - 118." type="journal article" year="1980">Wittmer, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Not in scale.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,220,595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Pronotum transverse, broadest next to apex; apex and base weakly arcuate, sides more strongly arcuate, apical corners rounded, basal corners strongly rounded; side margins distinct; disc moderately convex with coriaceous microsculpture and punctures, whose distance to each other equals 2–3 times their diameter; pubescence similar to that of head capsule. Elytra oblong-ovate; microsculpture, punctures and pubescence similar to those on pronotum; anteapically with circular impression. Front legs with tetramerous tarsi.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,220,595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
Pygidium (
<figureCitation box="[263,328,476,499]" captionStart="Figs 5–8" captionStartId="3.[113,150,1516,1535]" captionTargetBox="[188,1001,650,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[184,1019,624,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–8. Details of holotype of Colotrema socotrana sp. nov.5 – left maxillary palpus, ventral; 6 – pygidium, ventral view; 7 – sternite VIII, dorsal view; 8 – median lobe, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325783/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) with long basal struts, medially less sclerotized region, and bisinuate apex. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[320,381,508,531]" captionStart="Figs 5–8" captionStartId="3.[113,150,1516,1535]" captionTargetBox="[188,1001,650,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[184,1019,624,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–8. Details of holotype of Colotrema socotrana sp. nov.5 – left maxillary palpus, ventral; 6 – pygidium, ventral view; 7 – sternite VIII, dorsal view; 8 – median lobe, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325783/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with species-specific apex. Median lobe (
<figureCitation box="[822,883,508,531]" captionStart="Figs 5–8" captionStartId="3.[113,150,1516,1535]" captionTargetBox="[188,1001,650,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[184,1019,624,1510]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–8. Details of holotype of Colotrema socotrana sp. nov.5 – left maxillary palpus, ventral; 6 – pygidium, ventral view; 7 – sternite VIII, dorsal view; 8 – median lobe, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325783/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) subparallel at base and in middle, then conically widened, with 3–4 big endophallic sclerites in middle portion, and big bilateral ankylotic setae at apex.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325783" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5325783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325783/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" startId="3.[113,150,1516,1535]" targetBox="[188,1001,650,1482]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,1516,1562]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
Figs 5–8. Details of holotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Plonski, 2017" authorityName="Plonski" authorityYear="2017" box="[380,559,1516,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socotrana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[380,559,1516,1535]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Colotrema socotrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[563,628,1516,1535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
5 – left maxillary palpus, ventral; 6 – pygidium, ventral view; 7 – sternite VIII, dorsal view; 8 – median lobe, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,220,243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Variability.</emphasis>
The specimens of the 
<typeStatus box="[522,568,220,243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">type</typeStatus>
series vary considerably in elytral colouration from almost black elytra with only sides and apices near suture yellow (
<figureCitation box="[839,899,252,275]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[196,1075,222,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[170,1108,219,1517]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Habitus of Colotrema. 1–2 Colotrema socotrana sp. nov.: 1 – female allotype; 2 – male paratype 1; 3 – C. assirensis Wittmer, 1979; 4 – C. testacea wajjensis Wittmer, 1980. Not in scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325779" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325779/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) to elytra extensively yellow with black colour restricted to longitudinal club-shaped macula on the disc extending from humeral bulges to the apical third of elytra (
<figureCitation box="[678,742,316,339]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,188,1541,1560]" captionTargetBox="[196,1075,222,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[170,1108,219,1517]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Habitus of Colotrema. 1–2 Colotrema socotrana sp. nov.: 1 – female allotype; 2 – male paratype 1; 3 – C. assirensis Wittmer, 1979; 4 – C. testacea wajjensis Wittmer, 1980. Not in scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5325779" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5325779/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Sexual dimorphism. Males with longer antennae, modified apical maxillary palpomere, anteapical circular elytral impression and tetramerous fore tarsi. Females with shorter antennae, broad and apically truncated apical maxillary palpomere, pentamerous foretarsi, and without elytral impressions.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
Measurements.AL = 0.72–1.06 (
<typeStatus box="[522,616,476,499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[621,718,476,499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="0.91">0.91 mm</quantity>
); HW = 0.54–0.65 (
<typeStatus box="[919,1013,476,499]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[1018,1115,476,499]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8999999999999995" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="0.59">0.59 mm</quantity>
); IOW = 0.39–0.50 (
<typeStatus box="[349,444,508,531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[449,547,508,531]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="0.39">0.39 mm</quantity>
); PW = 0.65–0.76 (
<typeStatus box="[749,844,508,531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[849,947,508,531]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="0.65">0.65 mm</quantity>
); PL = 0.37–0.46 (
<typeStatus box="[158,251,540,563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[255,350,540,563]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="0.39">0.39 mm</quantity>
); EW = 0.91–1.09 (
<typeStatus box="[546,639,540,563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[643,737,540,563]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.6" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="0.96">0.96 mm</quantity>
); EL = 1.17–1.37 (
<typeStatus box="[924,1017,540,563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">holotype</typeStatus>
<quantity box="[1021,1116,540,563]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.17" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" unit="mm" value="1.17">1.17 mm</quantity>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,398,572,595]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Chromatically, 
<taxonomicName authority="Plonski, 2017" authorityName="Plonski" authorityYear="2017" box="[564,699,572,595]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socotrana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[564,699,572,595]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">C. socotrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[704,785,572,595]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to a group, whose members possess a completely orange pronotum and predominantly black elytra with yellow sides, apices and suture (the latter to varying extents). The most similar species is 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1991" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbertonica">
<emphasis box="[956,1126,636,659]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">C. barbertonica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="WITTMER W." box="[151,305,668,691]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" pagination="223 - 251" refId="ref2965" refString="WITTMER W. 1991: The genera Colotes Erichson and Colotrema Wittmer (Coleoptera: Malachiidae) mainly from southern Africa. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 35: 223 - 251." type="journal article" year="1991">Wittmer, 1991</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[371,510,668,691]" name="South Africa" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, which also possesses a completely orange coloured head capsule, but differs in having bicolorous extremities (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="WITTMER W." box="[747,957,700,723]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" pagination="223 - 251" refId="ref2965" refString="WITTMER W. 1991: The genera Colotes Erichson and Colotrema Wittmer (Coleoptera: Malachiidae) mainly from southern Africa. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 35: 223 - 251." type="journal article" year="1991">WITTMER 1991: 240</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName authority="Plonski, 2017" authorityName="Plonski" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socotrana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">C. socotrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[263,345,732,755]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is well characterized by the form of the male maxillary palpi (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="WITTMER W." pageId="4" pageNumber="129" pagination="223 - 251" refId="ref2965" refString="WITTMER W. 1991: The genera Colotes Erichson and Colotrema Wittmer (Coleoptera: Malachiidae) mainly from southern Africa. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 35: 223 - 251." type="journal article" year="1991">WITTMER 1991</bibRefCitation>
: Figs 49–50 for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1991" box="[391,564,764,787]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbertonica">
<emphasis box="[391,564,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">C. barbertonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the last abdominal segments. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authority="Plonski, 2017" authorityName="Plonski" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Colotrema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="socotrana" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">C. socotrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[264,347,796,819]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from the species occurring in the Arabian Peninsula by the characters given in the key below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="129" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,860,883]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is a Latin adjective derived from the place of origin and means ‘Socotran’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[151,680,924,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,220,947]" box="[151,680,924,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,924,947]" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Distribution.</emphasis>
Endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[433,589,924,947]" name="Socotra Island" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Socotra Island</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[598,676,924,947]" name="Yemen" pageId="4" pageNumber="129">Yemen</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
